<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1370,1575]" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1442,1467]" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[761,809,1443,1467]" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">type</typeStatus>
locality in 
<collectingCountry box="[946,1013,1442,1467]" name="Spain" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">Spain</collectingCountry>
. The specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[1262,1342,1442,1467]" name="Turkey" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">Turkey</collectingCountry>
slightly differs from the original description; specifically the legs are almost entirely black except light brownish red apical parts of fore and mid femora, fore and mid tibiae and bases of basitarsi. However, all other characters including peculiar bristling of the midlegs and genitalia are identical. This is the first record for 
<collectingCountry box="[1112,1194,1550,1575]" name="Turkey" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">Turkey</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
